race.comment: ALL FIRED UP (2) wasn't disgraced in city class at Belmont Park last time and the lead-up form reads well. Faces a far less daunting assignment this time and with the 3kg claim rates to be winning in this company. MY MONSTER (4) was better at Bunbury having his second race start. He can position forward and the blinkers are applied for the first time. Well placed and is sure to take plenty of stopping. NEK MINUTE (3) peaks on a quick backup. He was plain last time over longer but his effort at Kalgoorlie prior reads well enough. Gets another chance. HOT JELLY SHOT (6) finished midfield at Toodyay her first run back from a spell.  Has a 2kg claim and the winkers on first time. Fitter now and has scope for improvement.
